const bodyHtml = "<main>\n      <div class=\"site-shell article-layout\">\n        <article class=\"article\">\n          <a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-03-02 • Craft Flipping</a>\n          <h1>Best Enchant Book Craft Flips in Hypixel SkyBlock</h1>\n          <p class=\"lede\">Enchant books sit at one of the most interesting edges of craft flipping because they mix recipe math, convenience pricing and account progression. Buyers often pay a premium to skip combination ladders, collection requirements or awkward sourcing, but that premium only matters if the book is actually craftable, the ingredients are stable and the finished listing still sells at a useful pace.</p>\n\n          <div class=\"note\">\n            <strong>Primary source base:</strong> Recent expert based flipping guides that use book ladders as the clearest example of recipe arbitrage, convenience pricing and craftability discipline.\n          </div>\n\n          <h2>The spread is only the first filter</h2>\n          <p>Many players discover book flips by comparing the final book price against the visible cost of its parts and stopping there. That is not enough. You also need to know whether the ladder is available at your account stage, whether the ingredient inputs are moving too quickly to trust, and whether the finished book actually clears at a normal pace.</p>\n          <p>This is where book flips separate disciplined crafters from screenshot chasers. Enchant books can look amazing on paper and still become terrible capital sinks if you ignore access gates or sell speed.</p>\n\n          <h2>Why books keep a convenience premium</h2>\n          <p>Books are one of the cleanest examples of laziness tax in SkyBlock. Even players who could combine the parts themselves often prefer to buy the finished result because it saves time, inventory friction and uncertainty. The value is not the paper item by itself. The value is the skipped work.</p>\n          <p>That premium is strongest on books that remove annoying sourcing, shorten a progression step or cleanly compress multiple smaller purchases into one ready-to-use result.</p>\n\n          <h2>Use live tools to validate the ladder</h2>\n          <p>Live craft tools are essential because book routes can break quickly when ingredient prices move. <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bookFlips\">SkyCofl book flips</a> narrows the market to enchant combinations, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/crafts\">SkyCofl crafts</a> covers the wider basket, <a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/crafts\">Skyblock.bz crafts</a> ranks craft ROI in real time, <a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/craft-forge-flips\">BazaarPro craft and forge flips</a> adds more configurable scanning, and <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/crafts\">BazaarTracker crafts</a> helps confirm ingredient-side depth. The pattern should come from the guide. The final decision should come from today's live numbers.</p>\n\n          <h2>Read next</h2>\n          <ul class=\"related-list\">\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/craft-flipping-guide-2026\">Craft Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/seasonal-craft-flips-2026\">Seasonal Craft Flips in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/market-literacy-margin-volume-risk\">How to Read Margin, Volume and Risk Before You Flip</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n\n        <aside class=\"article-aside\">\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best paired tools</h3>\n            <ul class=\"tool-list\">\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bookFlips\">SkyCofl book flips</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/crafts\">SkyCofl crafts</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/fusion\">SkyCofl fusion</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/crafts\">Skyblock.bz crafts</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/feature